---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

import ProjectHeader from "../../components/ProjectHeader.astro";
import SmallHeading from "../../components/SmallHeading.astro";
import ProjectGrid from "../../components/ProjectGrid.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import preview from "../../images/fidelity/FDS.png";
import miro from "../../images/fidelity/miro.webm";
import miroMp4 from "../../images/fidelity/miro.mp4";
import miroPoster from "../../images/fidelity/miro-poster.jpg";
import uxr from "../../images/fidelity/uxr.png";

import sketching from "../../images/fidelity/sketching.png";
import discussions from "../../images/fidelity/discussions.png";

import dashboard from "../../images/fidelity/dashboard.png";
import editflow from "../../images/fidelity/edit-flow.png";
import addflow from "../../images/fidelity/add-flow.png";

import enrollment from "../../images/fidelity/enrollment.png";
import postenrollment from "../../images/fidelity/post-enrollment.png";

import painpoint from "../../images/fidelity/painpoint.png";
import painpoint2 from "../../images/fidelity/painpoint2.png";

import Link from "../../components/Link.astro";
import Caption from "../../components/Caption.astro";

import FrameCaption from "../../components/FrameCaption.astro";

import mainpage from "../../images/fidelity/main-page.png";
import mgmt from "../../images/fidelity/loan-mgmt.png";
import address from "../../images/fidelity/telling-the-user.png";
import changeloan from "../../images/fidelity/change-loan.png";
import mainbeforeafter from "../../images/fidelity/main-beforeafter.png";
import mgmtbeforeafter from "../../images/fidelity/mgmt-beforeafter.png";
---

<Layout title="Brian Sekelsky">
  <main>
    <ProjectHeader
      title="Fidelity Student Debt"
      objective="I spend my time at Fidelity working on complex B2B and B2C problems related to student debt. I joined the Student Debt Direct product to help modernize it, with an ambiguous brief to improve the post-enrollment experience. Working with the team, I implemented a new design system, fixed accessibility issues, and simplified the loan management experience."
      types={[
        "Product Design",
        "User Experience",
        "User Interface",
        "Visual Design",
      ]}
      collaborators={[]}
      year="2024"
      heroImage={preview}
      heroAlt="Screenshot of user experience work in figma"
    />
    <ProjectGrid>
      <div class="col-span-2">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 py-8">
          <Image
            class="shadow-sm"
            src={mainbeforeafter}
            alt="Before and after comparison of the main dashboard redesign"
          />
          <Image
            class="shadow-sm"
            src={mgmtbeforeafter}
            alt="Before and after comparison of the loan management page"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-1">
        <SmallHeading text="Learning the product" />
        <p>
          44 million Americans have student debt. Student Debt Direct is a
          workplace benefit that employers can offer to their employees through
          Fidelity. It is primarily a retention and hiring incentive where the
          employer agrees to pay some amount of their employee's student debt
          every month.
        </p>
        <p>
          The product requires complicated loan verification and management with
          cumbersome loan service provider systems. Regulatory changes ended plans
          to automate the verification process.
        </p>
        <p>
          My first move was to learn the existing product front to back. I sat
          down with our systems analyst and mapped the entire lifecycle of the
          product in Miro.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-1">
        <div class="relative">
          <video
            playsinline
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            preload="metadata"
            poster={miroPoster.src}
          >
            <source src={miro} type="video/webm" />
            <source src={miroMp4} type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
          <Caption text="UX lifecycles miro board" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- -->
      <div class="col-span-1">
        <SmallHeading text="Partnering with a UX researcher" />
        <p>
          Next, I partnered with our user experience researcher on a heuristic
          study. I even coded the frontend for a reference interface we used in
          the study.
        </p>
        <p>
          We worked through the product the way a user would, scenario by
          scenario, taking turns driving the reference interface and writing
          down everything that tripped us up. We also talked with a few people
          inside Fidelity who use the product, and their answers added to what
          we were finding on our own.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-1">
        <div class="relative">
          <Image
            class="shadow-sm"
            src={uxr}
            alt="Miro board alongside Visual Studio Code for reference UI development"
          />
          <Caption text="Miro board and screenshot from Visual Studio Code" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <SmallHeading text="Identifying pain points" />
        <p>
          Two findings stood out from our research. Users weren't clear on
          how loan management worked, and the communications around the
          product were causing confusion and frustration for employees
          trying to manage their benefits.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <Image
              class=""
              src={painpoint}
              alt="Research finding about loan management confusion"
            />
            <Caption text="Users aren't clear on loan management" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <Image
              class=""
              src={painpoint2}
              alt="Research finding about communication issues"
            />
            <Caption text="Communications are problematic" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-2 pt-8">
        <SmallHeading text="Lots of sketching and facilitating discussions" />
        <p class="lg:w-1/2">
          After we identified the pain points, I kept the conversation going
          with product owners, analysts, developers, and anyone else with a
          stake in the product. I deliberately kept my sketches rough and low
          fidelity. Pairing unpolished ideas with clear examples of the current
          product's problems made it easy for everyone to weigh in, and it gave
          the whole team a sense of ownership over the direction.
        </p>
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start py-8">
          <div class="lg:pl-4">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={discussions}
              alt="Zoom meeting with Miro board for collaborative ideation"
            />
            <Caption
              text="Discussions on Zoom, using Miro to collaborate on ideas"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="lg:pr-4">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={sketching}
              alt="Hand-drawn sketches and flow diagrams"
            />
            <Caption text="Sketching, primarily with flow diagrams" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-2 pt-8">
        <SmallHeading
          text="Solution: separating loan management into two flows"
        />
        <p class="lg:w-1/2">
          The most significant thing we built was a split of the complicated
          loan management procedure into two separate flows. If a user just
          needs to edit an existing loan, we give them one short, focused
          experience. If their situation is more involved and they need to add
          a new loan, we give them a different one. Users can also add
          additional loans and see a historical record of their accounts, which
          builds trust and makes it easy to swap in the loan they most want
          paid off first.
        </p>

        <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 py-8">
          <div class="lg:pl-4">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={dashboard}
              alt="Redesigned dashboard with separate edit and add loan actions"
            />
            <Caption
              text="New additions to the dashboard include separate actions for editing and adding loans"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="lg:pr-4">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={editflow}
              alt="Edit loan flow wireframes"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <div>
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={addflow}
              alt="Add new loan flow wireframes"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-2 pt-8">
        <SmallHeading text="Moving to a new design system" />
        <p class="lg:w-1/2">
          Fidelity is overhauling its design system and working to unify all of
          its products, with component reuse and accessibility as priorities
          for the business. I am helping establish consistent patterns, like
          the way you edit an account, throughout the enterprise experience.
        </p>

        <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 py-8">
          <div class="lg:pl-4">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={mainpage}
              alt="Post-enrollment dashboard with new design system"
            />
            <Caption text="Updated look for the post-enrollment dashboard" />
          </div>
          <div class="lg:pr-4">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={mgmt}
              alt="Loan management interface with new design patterns"
            />
            <Caption text="Updated look and pattern for loan management" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-2 pt-8">
        <SmallHeading text="Telling the user what's wrong" />
        <p class="lg:w-1/2">
          In the final iterations of the design, we introduced inline alerts
          that tell users when there are problems with their loan. Each alert
          explains what is wrong and how to fix it, so users can get back to
          receiving payments.
        </p>

        <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 py-8">
          <div class="lg:pl-4">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={address}
              alt="Loan management showing inline alert about payment address issues"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="lg:pr-4">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={changeloan}
              alt="Change loan interface with error state handling"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </ProjectGrid>
  </main>
</Layout>
